Experiment No.: 04
Date:17/09/2025

Title:
Binary to Decimal & Octal to Hexadecimal Conversion

AIM:
To develop a Python program to convert a binary number to its decimal equivalent and an octal number to its hexadecimal
equivalent using functions.

Algorithm:
1. Start the program.
2. Define a function binary_to_decimal(binary) to:
• Convert the binary string to a decimal integer using int(binary, 2).
• Return the decimal value.
3. Define another function octal_to_hexadecimal(octal) to:
• Convert the octal string to a decimal integer using int(octal, 8).
• Convert the decimal value to hexadecimal using hex().
• Return the hexadecimal value.
4. Input a binary number and an octal number from the user.
5. Call both functions and display the converted values.
6. Stop the program.

Python Program (Source Code):
# Program to convert binary to decimal
# and octal to hexadecimal using functions
# Function to convert binary to decimal
def binary_to_decimal(binary):
  return int(binary, 2)
# Function to convert octal to hexadecimal
def octal_to_hexadecimal(octal):
  decimal_value = int(octal, 8)
  return hex(decimal_value)
# Input from user
binary_num = input("Enter a binary number: ")
octal_num = input("Enter an octal number: ")
# Conversions
decimal_result = binary_to_decimal(binary_num)
hex_result = octal_to_hexadecimal(octal_num)
# Display results
print("Binary to Decimal Conversion:", decimal_result)
print("Octal to Hexadecimal Conversion:", hex_result)

Output:
Enter a binary number:1010
Enter an octal number:6735
Binary to decimal conversion :10
Octal to hexadecimal conversion: 0xddd

Result:
Thus, the Python program to convert binary to decimal and octal to hexadecimal using functions was successfully written,
executed, and verified.
